{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"verify"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"identity"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnectableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO20SocketConnectableRefV","text":"SocketConnectableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"trustedCa"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSCertificateRefV","text":"TLSCertificateRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO19TLSCertificateFlagsV","text":"TLSCertificateFlags"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cert"},{"type":"text","text":" is valid, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_TLS_CERTIFICATE_NO_FLAGS"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identity"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cert"},{"type":"text","text":"â€™s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name(s)"},{"type":"text","text":" will be compared against"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_TLS_CERTIFICATE_BAD_IDENTITY"},{"type":"text","text":" will be set in the return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value if it does not match. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identity"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", that bit will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"never be set in the return value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trusted_ca"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cert"},{"type":"text","text":" (or one of the certificates"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in its chain) must be signed by it, or else"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_TLS_CERTIFICATE_UNKNOWN_CA"},{"type":"text","text":" will be set in the return value. If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trusted_ca"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", that bit will never be set in the return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib guarantees that if certificate verification fails, at least one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error will be set in the return value, but it does not guarantee"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that all possible errors will be set. Accordingly, you may not safely"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"decide to ignore any particular type of error. For example, it would"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be incorrect to mask "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_TLS_CERTIFICATE_EXPIRED"},{"type":"text","text":" if you want to allow"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expired certificates, because this could potentially be the only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error flag set even if other problems exist with the certificate."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because TLS session context is not used, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsCertificate"},{"type":"text","text":" may not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"perform as many checks on the certificates as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" would."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, certificate constraints may not be honored, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"revocation checks may not be performed. The best way to verify TLS"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"certificates used by a TLS connection is to let "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handle the verification."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tlscertificateprotocol\/verify(identity:trustedca:)-5b8gu"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateProtocol\/verify(identity:trustedCa:)-5b8gu","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This verifies "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cert"},{"type":"text","text":" and returns a set of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsCertificateFlags"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indicating any problems found with it. This can be used to verify a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"certificate outside the context of making a connection, or to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"check a certificate against a CA that is not part of the system"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"CA database."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"verify(identity:trustedCa:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"verify"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"identity"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","te